No. No. I'm sorry.

21:19.340 --> 21:22.630
I was thinking about Jack.

21:22.710 --> 21:26.260
He hears the results of
his evaluation tomorrow.

21:28.180 --> 21:31.100
I have no idea how
he's gonna react.

21:31.180 --> 21:35.640
Feels like everything is on
such shaky ground these days.

21:36.940 --> 21:39.360
It's the war.

21:39.440 --> 21:41.520
The whole world has gone crazy.

21:45.190 --> 21:47.410
Can I ask you something?

21:47.490 --> 21:49.410
Mm-hmm.

21:49.490 --> 21:51.740
When we were with your father,

21:51.830 --> 21:54.750
and he gave me his blessing...

21:54.830 --> 21:57.290
maybe it was just
my imagination,

21:57.370 --> 22:01.210
and I-I don't mean
to beat a dead horse...

22:01.290 --> 22:04.090
It wasn't just your imagination.

22:06.840 --> 22:09.760
I guess I never
understood before,

22:09.840 --> 22:13.060
but I'm starting to get it.

22:14.060 --> 22:15.890
Get what?

22:15.980 --> 22:18.060
Just be nice to know

22:18.140 --> 22:21.360
that someone's gonna be there
for you, no matter what.

22:29.240 --> 22:30.910
Come in.

22:36.040 --> 22:38.920
I can't tell you how
good it is to see you.

22:40.880 --> 22:42.420
You can thank Patty for that.

22:42.500 --> 22:43.800
She insisted on it.

22:43.880 --> 22:46.590
She's in the library.

22:46.670 --> 22:48.800
But she wanted to talk
to Virgil alone.

22:50.180 --> 22:52.180
It's okay, Mabel.

22:53.720 --> 22:56.100
Here, let me show you
the garden.

23:00.060 --> 23:02.060
Patty?

23:05.900 --> 23:07.280
You look well.

23:07.360 --> 23:09.110
You don't.

23:09.200 --> 23:11.320
Well, it's been
a hard few years.

23:11.410 --> 23:12.490
Why?

23:12.570 --> 23:14.280
You won.

23:14.370 --> 23:16.580
These are overrun
with horn worms.

23:16.660 --> 23:18.370
If someone doesn't deal
with them,

23:18.450 --> 23:20.460
they'll kill the whole plant.

23:24.920 --> 23:26.840
How do you do it?

23:26.920 --> 23:29.090
Go on pretending.

23:31.130 --> 23:33.550
You couldn't
possibly understand.

23:37.600 --> 23:39.680
I've lost both my children.

23:41.390 --> 23:44.480
Maybe someday you'll know
what it is to be a mother.

23:44.560 --> 23:46.520
<i>The Magus is in prison.</i>

23:46.610 --> 23:48.400
Jack's career hangs
in the balance.

23:48.480 --> 23:50.570
There must be
some satisfaction in that.

23:50.650 --> 23:53.320
Uh, everything I have
done was to save you.

23:53.410 --> 23:54.990
From what?

23:55.070 --> 23:57.030
- These heathens?
- No.

23:57.120 --> 23:58.540
From yourself.

23:58.620 --> 24:00.660
I didn't need to be saved,
Daddy.

24:03.120 --> 24:04.880
Susan said on the phone

24:04.960 --> 24:07.040
that you were considering
coming home.

24:07.130 --> 24:09.880
Truth is, it stopped being fun
around here.

24:09.960 --> 24:12.880
Maybe there <i>is</i> such a thing
as too much freedom.

24:14.800 --> 24:16.550
But there's something
you'll need to do

24:16.640 --> 24:20.060
before I'll ever
step foot in that house.

24:20.140 --> 24:23.440
Swear you'll never
touch me again.

25:04.810 --> 25:06.560
It might bring you
some relief to know

25:06.650 --> 25:10.110
that Dr. Grisby found you
of fundamentally sound mind.

25:10.190 --> 25:11.900
He believes

25:11.980 --> 25:15.280
that the delusion you suffered
was a result of...

25:15.360 --> 25:18.910
Exhaustion psychosis.

25:18.990 --> 25:20.280
You've been working too hard.

25:20.370 --> 25:22.450
Exacerbated

25:22.540 --> 25:25.670
by excessive narcotic
and alcohol consumption.

25:25.750 --> 25:27.710
Which comes as no surprise
to all of us here.

25:27.790 --> 25:29.750
The general

25:29.840 --> 25:32.300
and I appreciate
all you've done,

25:32.380 --> 25:36.130
and recognize that the next
phase in the rocketry program

25:36.220 --> 25:39.510
was due in large part
to your efforts.

25:39.600 --> 25:41.310
For that reason,

25:41.390 --> 25:43.310
they have insisted that you
be offered some sort

25:43.390 --> 25:46.640
of ongoing role,
against my recommendation...

25:46.730 --> 25:49.520
Well, why didn't
you just say so?

25:49.610 --> 25:51.190
As a fuel technician.

25:54.110 --> 25:55.360
We could not

25:55.440 --> 25:56.650
in good conscience

25:56.740 --> 25:59.700
put you in any position
of authority.

26:00.910 --> 26:03.700
Then who's gonna run JPL?

26:03.790 --> 26:05.330
Mr. Onsted.

26:05.410 --> 26:07.580
Who else?

26:11.460 --> 26:13.380
You'd still be
inside the operation.

26:13.460 --> 26:15.050
Of course you'd be happy.

26:15.130 --> 26:16.896
- They crowned you king.
- You can't seriously expect

26:16.920 --> 26:18.906
to be put into a position
where you could jeopardize

26:18.930 --> 26:20.550
- the project again.
- Where's Patty?

26:20.640 --> 26:23.350
- She went home, Mr. Parsons.
- What does she have to do with this?

26:23.430 --> 26:25.850
- I need someone who's on my side.
- I'm on your side.

26:25.930 --> 26:27.156
He's been trying to push you out

26:27.180 --> 26:28.390
from the start.

26:28.480 --> 26:29.650
I told you,

26:29.730 --> 26:30.860
this was a mistake.

26:30.940 --> 26:32.060
You're damn right.

26:32.150 --> 26:34.190
I built this
entire scientific field.

26:34.280 --> 26:37.190
- Mr. Parsons, please.
- I don't need to be part of JPL.

26:37.280 --> 26:38.570
Last I checked,

26:38.650 --> 26:39.966
I'm still president
of this company,

26:39.990 --> 26:41.490
and we don't need them.

26:41.570 --> 26:43.990
This was a devil's bargain.

26:44.080 --> 26:46.040
We need to turn our focus
back to the stars

26:46.120 --> 26:48.040
instead of building
their weapons of war.

26:48.120 --> 26:50.080
You were a goddamn janitor
when we met.

26:50.170 --> 26:52.380
